This paper deals with the capacity of relay networks, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of filter-and-forward relay nodes is common in many communication systems, which suggests that the paper could also be categorized under networked systems (cs.NI) or control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of simulation results, which suggests that it could be categorized under multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper deals with coding strategies for automatic repeat request (ARQ) or hybrid-ARQ, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cryptography and security (cs.CR).
